\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {The familiar bustle of Edenfield University felt hollow to Will as he navigated its pathways. Gone was his usual easy smile, replaced by a grim determination etched on his face. In his right hand, a wad of flyers emblazoned with the chilling words "Missing Person" served as a constant reminder of their plight. Ashley's smiling face, captured in the accompanying photo, only amplified the weight that settled on his heart with each step.}
\par\plain {Will wasn't alone in his mission. Madeleine, her presence a silent pillar of support, walked beside him. The once vibrant campus, teeming with student life, now seemed muted, the usual chatter replaced by hushed whispers that followed them like worried shadows. Every curious glance that lingered on their grim expressions fueled Will's urgency.}
\par\plain {With each poster he slapped onto a surface - a telephone pole, a wall, a bulletin board - a flicker of hope ignited, only to be extinguished by the harsh reality of the situation. His hands trembled slightly as he secured another one, the stark contrast between Ashley's beaming smile and the stark words above it a constant punch to the gut.}
\par\plain {Madeleine's voice, a beacon of unwavering belief, pierced through the fog of despair clouding his mind. "Will," she said, her hand finding his, "we're going to find her. I can feel it."}
\par\plain {Will yearned to share her optimism. "I wish I could too, Madeleine," he sighed, his voice heavy with a weariness that belied the short time since Ashley's disappearance. "But it's been almost a day, and the police have nothing. I feel... powerless."}
\par\plain {"I understand," Madeleine offered gently, her grip tightening on his hand. "But giving up hope isn't an option. Ashley wouldn't want that."}
\par\plain {Will squeezed her hand back, a flicker of defiance igniting within him. "You're right," he conceded, straightening his shoulders as they continued their walk. "Ashley wouldn't want to be kidnapped in the first place," he muttered, his voice laced with anger.}
\par\plain {Their journey continued, a silent promise hanging heavy in the air. They would plaster Ashley's face on every surface, their determination a testament to their unwavering friendship. As they moved from building to building, Will's mind churned with the unanswered questions that gnawed at him like a relentless predator. But amidst the fear and desperation, a spark of hope remained alive, fueled by Madeleine's unwavering belief and their shared love for their missing friend. They would find Ashley. They had to.}
